the doors off all our rooms.

06:26.604 --> 06:28.393
That'd be really bad for <i> you,</i> Oliver.

06:28.394 --> 06:30.223
I have nothing to hide.

06:30.224 --> 06:33.566
But, at the same time,
we do need to cover this up,

06:33.591 --> 06:36.183
and the only way we're gonna
do that is if we stick together.

06:36.184 --> 06:39.983
Like this slice of pizza
attached to Taylor's math book?

06:39.984 --> 06:42.434
<i>That's</i> why third period is so confusing!

06:44.684 --> 06:47.523
- Oh. Your hand is so big.
- Thanks.

06:47.524 --> 06:48.773
I feel very safe right now.

06:48.774 --> 06:49.983
I'm so glad.

06:49.984 --> 06:52.144
- Doris, let's compare hands.
- Oh!

06:52.145 --> 06:53.183
Ow!

06:53.184 --> 06:54.603
Knock it off!

06:54.604 --> 06:57.433
Oh, God. Greg is going for
one of his skinny poetry books.

06:57.434 --> 06:58.983
Those are the worst kinds.

06:58.984 --> 06:59.894
Who's in the mood for a sonnet?

06:59.894 --> 07:00.814
- No.
- Almost.

07:00.815 --> 07:02.183
