12:15.585 --> 12:17.664
- Can you help, please?
- One sec.

12:17.689 --> 12:20.451
I'm trying to get this paint off
my Nordstrom's not Rack shirt.

12:21.447 --> 12:23.163
There! It's ruined!

12:23.188 --> 12:24.219
Now help!

12:24.253 --> 12:25.383
Well, let's see how <i> you</i> like it!

12:27.218 --> 12:29.845
Joke's on you. These are my bib pants!

12:32.081 --> 12:33.438
Guys!

12:34.765 --> 12:36.092
Holy [bleep]!

12:36.117 --> 12:37.870
Oh, my God. It went through
the wall. What do we do now?

12:37.895 --> 12:40.609
First, we watch our language.

12:43.001 --> 12:45.574
The drive is just the first leg.

12:45.599 --> 12:47.330
Next up is the train.

12:47.331 --> 12:50.410
If I catch the 7:21,

12:50.411 --> 12:53.540
I get into the city at 8:28.

12:53.541 --> 12:56.223
But if I catch the 7:26,

12:56.248 --> 12:58.575
I get there at 8:45.

12:58.600 --> 13:00.497
Please... tell us more.

13:00.522 --> 13:02.210
Unh-unh. Stop punishing us

13:02.211 --> 13:04.120
by encouraging Richard
to talk about his commute.

13:04.121 --> 13:06.210
All we said was that therapy
was a good thing!

13:06.235 --> 13:07.672
And that <i> I'm</i> the problem.

13:07.727 --> 13:09.655
Right! You get it!

13:09.680 --> 13:11.593
Just so you know, you two are the ones

13:11.618 --> 13:13.179
who should be in couples therapy.

13:13.204 --> 13:15.370
<i>You</i> can't keep your muskrat in its cage!

13:15.417 --> 13:17.206
What does that mean?

13:17.207 --> 13:18.826
You are so pretty.

13:18.827 --> 13:21.886
And <i> you</i> bag on your husband constantly!

13:22.497 --> 13:24.116
You talk about me?

13:24.117 --> 13:25.706
Aww.

13:25.707 --> 13:28.456
Okay, everyone, look.
Katie is projecting.

13:28.457 --> 13:31.914
Sometimes we have pent-up anger,
and we choose to lash out.

13:31.939 --> 13:32.976
No!

13:33.001 --> 13:35.286
This is not what this is.

13:35.287 --> 13:36.826
I lied.

13:36.827 --> 13:38.246
Greg and I aren't in therapy.

13:38.247 --> 13:39.416
I made the whole thing up

13:39.417 --> 13:40.960
just so I didn't
have to tell you the truth.

13:40.985 --> 13:42.360
The real reason we canceled

13:42.385 --> 13:44.921
is because dinners at your house
are the worst!

13:44.946 --> 13:47.632
Ah! I'll put <i> any</i> dinner at my house

13:47.657 --> 13:50.296
up against this garbage party
full of poetry and lies!

13:50.321 --> 13:52.860
And I suppose you lied
about Greg's ruptured colon

13:52.885 --> 13:54.786
to get out of going
to that sound bath with me.

13:54.787 --> 13:56.656
Why are you always giving me
medical problems?

13:56.657 --> 13:58.156
It's so easy to buy!

13:58.157 --> 13:59.689
You look disease-y, Greg.

13:59.714 --> 14:01.956
Okay, look, everybody calm down.

14:01.957 --> 14:03.036
You're right.

14:03.037 --> 14:04.956
And to put this in perspective,

14:04.957 --> 14:06.786
perhaps a poetry reading.

14:09.117 --> 14:11.996
I think Anne Sexton said it best...

14:11.997 --> 14:14.706
You think we're the only ones
she lies to?

14:14.707 --> 14:16.656
- She forgot about your birthday.
- What?

14:16.657 --> 14:19.821
And she threw this dinner party
at the last second as a cover.

14:19.883 --> 14:20.928
I don't believe it.

14:20.953 --> 14:21.996
Yeah, I do.

14:21.997 --> 14:23.656
Come on, Richard. We're leaving.

14:23.720 --> 14:25.349
But it's finally fun!

14:25.404 --> 14:26.774
Crissy, let's go.

14:38.207 --> 14:41.326
You forgot my birthday
and then lied about it.

14:41.327 --> 14:42.416
I did.

14:42.417 --> 14:44.203
But before you get too mad, remember...

14:44.250 --> 14:46.391
- your blood pressure is high.
- Right.

14:46.416 --> 14:48.578
Wait, is it? I don't know
what to believe anymore!

14:55.917 --> 14:57.656
I'm glad you decided to come.

14:57.657 --> 14:59.663
- We want to talk about last night.
- Yeah.

14:59.688 --> 15:01.956
I'm confused.
You have a breakfast at home,

15:01.957 --> 15:03.746
and then you come here
for another breakfast?

15:03.747 --> 15:05.172
Why is he not getting this?

15:06.117 --> 15:08.286
The pretty ones are sometimes slow.

15:08.311 --> 15:09.892
Mnh.

15:09.917 --> 15:11.194
Let's get down to it.

15:11.219 --> 15:12.996
Katie needs to be stopped.

15:12.997 --> 15:15.496
I agree. Her lying has become
a problem for all of us.

15:15.497 --> 15:18.656
She needs to be confronted,
<i>and</i> my pal Crissy can help.

15:18.657 --> 15:20.790
Downgraded to "pal" already, huh?

15:20.815 --> 15:23.359
Yeah, well, I've been making
eyes with the new waitress.

15:23.384 --> 15:26.032
She's... Oh. Nope.

15:26.057 --> 15:28.109
Nope, she's just
putting in her contact lens.

15:28.134 --> 15:30.286
My girlfriend, Crissy, can help.

15:33.917 --> 15:37.132
I got your text.
Where's James Van Der Beek?

15:37.157 --> 15:38.576
Not here.

15:38.577 --> 15:39.942
This is an intervention.

15:39.967 --> 15:42.114
I shaved above the knee for this?

15:42.139 --> 15:43.676
We're here to talk about your lying.

15:43.701 --> 15:44.656
I would love to,

15:44.657 --> 15:46.863
but I have to take Greg
to his colonoscopy.

15:46.888 --> 15:48.245
You have a real problem.

15:49.849 --> 15:52.019
Katie, please have a seat.

15:55.957 --> 15:58.469
Your lying has caused a rift
in your relationships,

15:58.494 --> 16:00.039
and you need to start telling the truth.

16:00.064 --> 16:02.036
Maybe <i> you</i> need
to start telling the truth.

16:02.037 --> 16:05.076
- You're not licensed to do that.
- Fine.

16:05.077 --> 16:07.076
Let's just get this over with.

16:07.077 --> 16:09.346
Okay. What are some of the lies

16:09.371 --> 16:12.319
that you've told
Doris, Angela, and Greg?

16:12.344 --> 16:13.394
Okay.

16:14.617 --> 16:17.217
Doris, remember you gave me money

16:17.242 --> 16:19.420
to bet on red when I went to Foxwoods?

16:19.445 --> 16:21.037
I lied. You didn't lose.

16:21.062 --> 16:23.273
I spent the money on a giant daiquiri.

16:24.295 --> 16:27.271
Now, Doris, remember, what do we say?

16:28.242 --> 16:30.411
Thank you for your honesty.

16:30.412 --> 16:31.661
You're welcome.

16:31.662 --> 16:34.451
Angela, remember
when you aligned my chakras

16:34.452 --> 16:37.201
and I told you it made me
less aggravated with my kids?

16:37.202 --> 16:39.901
When I got home, I sat on Oliver.

16:41.042 --> 16:42.471
Thank you for your honesty.

16:43.832 --> 16:44.991
Greg, you know how I told you

16:44.992 --> 16:46.741
I stopped using veal in the meatloaf

16:46.742 --> 16:48.653
because you didn't want
to eat little cows?

16:48.678 --> 16:50.919
- Don't say it. Don't say it.
- Didn't stop.

16:50.944 --> 16:52.703
So sad.

16:52.704 --> 16:54.703
So tender.

16:54.704 --> 16:57.153
Katie, why are you lying?

16:57.154 --> 16:58.371
You don't seem like the kind of person

16:58.396 --> 16:59.582
who's afraid to tell the truth.

16:59.607 --> 17:01.823
No. I'm not.

17:01.824 --> 17:03.823
I can do some crowd work to prove it.

17:03.824 --> 17:05.613
Hey, you! Laptop!

17:05.614 --> 17:06.880
For the last month,

17:06.905 --> 17:08.782
I have read that screenplay
over your shoulder,

17:08.784 --> 17:10.653
and it is <i> terrible.</i>

17:10.654 --> 17:12.823
If you're not afraid
to tell the truth to a stranger,

17:12.824 --> 17:14.323
then why do you feel
the need to lie to <i> us,</i>

17:14.324 --> 17:15.363
the people you love?

17:15.364 --> 17:18.422
I lie <i>because</i> I love you.

17:18.446 --> 17:21.573
- What?
- I don't want to hurt your feelings.

17:21.574 --> 17:24.403
And I want to keep putting veal
in my meatloaf.

17:24.404 --> 17:26.863
Katie, you told a lot of truths today.

17:26.864 --> 17:28.906
Are there any truths
you <i> haven't</i> told yet?

17:30.404 --> 17:31.494
There are.

17:33.094 --> 17:36.883
Doris, I know I have told you
that you're too harsh,

17:36.946 --> 17:38.695
but the truth is...

17:38.744 --> 17:41.635
you are the strongest person
that I know.

17:42.614 --> 17:44.363
Thank you for your honesty.

17:44.364 --> 17:46.356
And, Angela, I know sometimes

17:46.434 --> 17:49.176
I make fun of you for being a softie...

17:49.244 --> 17:52.598
but you are the kindest person
I've ever met.

17:52.947 --> 17:55.736
Thank you, Katie, for your honesty.

17:55.784 --> 17:59.118
And, Greg, the truth is...

17:59.204 --> 18:01.782
you are the best person that I know.

18:01.864 --> 18:03.508
Period.

18:03.574 --> 18:05.118
I love you.

18:05.154 --> 18:07.819
And I am so sorry
that I forgot your birthday.

18:07.844 --> 18:08.844
That's okay.

18:08.869 --> 18:10.028
I love you, too.

18:11.896 --> 18:13.655
And while we're on this truth train,

18:13.704 --> 18:17.014
you seem like a nice person, so...

18:17.074 --> 18:19.324
- get out now.
- Really?

18:20.606 --> 18:22.613
Are you gonna cheat on me?

18:23.312 --> 18:26.401
Girl, I don't know
what you got going on today,

18:26.426 --> 18:28.703
but you are looking fine!

18:28.704 --> 18:29.903
Mm!

18:47.324 --> 18:48.703
If she didn't clean her room,

18:48.704 --> 18:49.993
you're going to read her poetry.

18:49.994 --> 18:51.790
Culture should not be a punishment.

18:51.815 --> 18:53.815
But it <i> is.</i>

18:54.814 --> 18:56.153
You ready to show me the room yet?

18:56.154 --> 18:57.444
Come on in!

18:58.614 --> 19:01.175
Anna-Kat, do you have any 6s?

19:01.200 --> 19:03.113
Sorry, Oliver. Go fish!

19:03.138 --> 19:04.427
Taylor?

19:04.428 --> 19:05.678
What did you do?

19:07.848 --> 19:10.177
You cleaned your room!

19:10.178 --> 19:12.007
Cleaned <i>and</i> reorganized.

19:12.008 --> 19:13.033
Well, technically,

19:13.058 --> 19:15.181
"reorganized" implies
that it was once organized,

19:15.206 --> 19:16.478
but good job, kiddo.

19:17.428 --> 19:18.927
So good.

19:18.928 --> 19:21.217
It looks great!

19:21.218 --> 19:22.565
How long are we gonna
keep this a secret?

19:22.590 --> 19:24.007
Until I go to college.

19:24.008 --> 19:25.427
No, until <i> I</i> go to college.

19:25.428 --> 19:26.467
You're both saying the same thing.

19:32.178 --> 19:34.458
Happy birthday!

19:34.548 --> 19:38.098
From now on, I won't be such a liar.

19:38.178 --> 19:39.638
- Thanks, babe.
- Mm-hmm.

19:40.848 --> 19:42.637
Oh.

19:42.638 --> 19:45.157
A coupon for
one free intellectual salon.

19:45.182 --> 19:46.704
You can invite all your boring friends.

19:46.729 --> 19:48.048
You can talk about
all the crap you want.

19:48.073 --> 19:50.579
- You can wear whatever dumb outfit...
- Unh-unh-unh-unh.

19:50.604 --> 19:52.047
You know what?

19:52.048 --> 19:53.307
To Hell with Crissy.

19:53.308 --> 19:55.709
Maybe a healthy marriage
is based on lies.

19:55.734 --> 19:58.260
Then ours is the best.

19:59.712 --> 20:00.990
Thanks.

20:04.508 --> 20:06.018
Now that Taylor's left,

20:06.043 --> 20:07.257
the house feels so empty.

20:07.298 --> 20:10.364
But we can finally do
what we want with this room!

20:10.389 --> 20:12.771
Let's get rid of this bed
and put in a giant hot tub.

20:13.959 --> 20:15.076
What the hell?!

20:16.048 --> 20:17.888
What the hell?

20:20.008 --> 20:22.137
"Dear Mom and Dad,
by the time you read this,

20:22.138 --> 20:24.287
the statute of limitations
will have run out.

20:24.312 --> 20:26.307
Signed... Taylor, Anna-Kat, and Oliver."

20:26.308 --> 20:27.717
Oh!

20:27.718 --> 20:30.366
That explains why Taylor
had books in her room.

20:31.678 --> 20:35.066
Well, this is very troubling.

20:35.113 --> 20:36.127
Mm.

20:36.152 --> 20:38.580
We obviously can't have
your salon tonight, Greg.

20:40.098 --> 20:41.511
Then when?!

